replies.comment info:
@Angelina, Miciah, Bella, Lizzy 
You're right about the number of seats gained balancing the number of seats lost - that is necessary in order to keep the total number of seats in the House set at 435. 
You might dig a bit farther with your "wonder" statement about Texas. How much did it go up from the 2010 census to the 2020 census, and as a result, what percent of all Americans are from Texas now versus what that percent was back in 2010? Also, what can you find out why Texas' population is growing as it is from 2010 to 2020?
